import React, { useState } from 'react' import PropTypes from 'prop-types' export default function Navbar(props) { const [textMode, setTextMode]=useState('light') textMode=()=>{ if (props.mode=='dark'){ setTextMode= 'light' } else (props.mode='li') } return (
{props.title}
  • {props.home}
  • {props.elementAbout}
) } Navbar.propTypes = { title: PropTypes.string, elementAbout: PropTypes.string, home: PropTypes.string } Navbar.defaultProps = { title: 'TextUtils', elementAbout: "About", home: "Home" }
